$ /media/vdc/code/ai/loreloop/.venv/bin/python -m loreloop.cli knowledge export --help

[stdout]
usage: loreloop knowledge export [-h] [--stale]
                                 [--format {audit,package,docs}]
                                 [--output OUTPUT]
                                 [--project-name PROJECT_NAME]
                                 [--requirements PATH] [--force] [--attest]

options:
  -h, --help            show this help message and exit
  --stale               audit only: export entries with drifted code anchors
  --format {audit,package,docs}
                        audit entries or deterministic project package; docs
                        is a compatibility alias
  --output OUTPUT       audit Markdown file, source-docs directory, or
                        deliverable .zip package; package/docs defaults to
                        baseline.zip
  --project-name PROJECT_NAME
                        project name used in source documents
  --requirements PATH   committed Markdown requirements; use repo:NAME/path
                        for a peer repository
  --force               replace an existing ZIP or update source docs in a
                        non-empty directory
  --attest              append an optional local trust-chain attestation for
                        the exported package

